list.abstract: Team Dignitas是一支总部位于英国的电子竞技战队，在2003年9月9日成立。 2019年1月5日，Dignitas通过官方推特宣布从即日起正式退出绝地求生项目，并解散其战队。2023年11月30日，DIG官宣和Rich续约。
dig 　　 DIG传媒集团 　　DIG（Data mining and Intelligent panoramic Media Group）——数据挖掘与全景智能传播媒体集团。

yingyinNormal.en: What is that? I'll send a dig team.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那是个什么玩意？我派一个挖掘队过去。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay. Well, I would like to do a dig in the Painted Desert.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们会在沙漠里进行挖掘。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, there's this guy, Warren, from the museum and he's going on a dig for like two years and he's got this great place he needs to sublet. So, you interested?
yingyinNormal.zh: 好，我们博物馆有个华伦，要去参与挖掘工作2年，他有个漂亮的家要转租，你有兴趣吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Let's dig it out. It's a metal coin. Treasure. Hooray.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们把它挖出来。这是一枚硬币。是宝藏！好棒！

yingyinNormal.en: Now, what shall we do? Easy. We'll dig up the road.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在我们该怎么办？这简单，我们来把路给挖开吧。

yingyinNormal.en: How are you going to fix it? We dig up the road. Wow.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你们要怎么修理呢？我们要把路给挖开！哇！

yingyinNormal.en: So you're determined to dig in your heels. I am sorry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你是打算固执己见了，很抱歉。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm not really a part of this, so I'm just gonna dig in.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我没有参与这些事，我好好坐下来听吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, what shall we do? Easy. We'll dig up the road. Hooray.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在我们该怎么办？这简单，我们来把路给挖开吧。好哎！

yingyinNormal.en: How do you mend electrical cables? We dig up the road. Hooray.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那么你要怎么做才能把电缆修好呢？我们要把路再挖开！太棒了！

yingyinNormal.en: Set your house in order, and dig in for the battle to survive.
yingyinNormal.zh: 安顿好你的船，准备打场持久战。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes, while also getting in a solid dig at you. Pretty efficient?
yingyinNormal.zh: 没错，我还同时好好挖苦了你一番，这才叫一石二鸟。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes, it is. And you can dig yourself out. Because I've had enough.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没错，你自己来解决吧，因为我受够了。

yingyinNormal.en: Mr. Bull, how are you going to mend the hole? We'll dig up the road.
yingyinNormal.zh: 公牛先生，你知道怎么修好这个洞吗？我们要把路挖开。

yingyinNormal.en: Mr. Bull, how are you going to mend the hole? We'll dig up the road.
yingyinNormal.zh: 公牛先生，你知道怎么修好这个洞吗？我们要把路挖开。

yingyinNormal.en: Daddy Pig. You're just in time to help us dig a hole. Yes, of course.
yingyinNormal.zh: 猪爸爸。你来得正好，帮我们挖一个坑。好的没问题。

yingyinNormal.en: It was torture seeing him dig up my grass. How could my father let him do this?
yingyinNormal.zh: 看他在我的草地上挖洞，让我很难受。为什么爸爸允许他挖洞？

yingyinNormal.en: This is so nice. Thank you for doing this. Oh, please. Cooking soothes me. So, dig in.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真好，谢谢你这么费心。别客气，烹饪能舒缓我的心，吃吧，好。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, sure. "Dear..?" Sarah. "Sarah. I dig you. Dr. Ross Geller." Oh, Thank you So much.
yingyinNormal.zh: 喔，当然。亲爱的？莎拉。“莎拉，我挖（喜欢）你”。“罗斯盖勒博士上”。哇，真是太谢谢你了。

yingyinNormal.en: How would I react to Jay's speech? Give me "Touched." Now sad. Sadder. Come on. Dig deep.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对于杰的演讲，我应该有什么反应？表现出感动的样子，悲伤，再悲伤点。加油，感情再深点。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Airborne technologies allow archaeologists to learn about what lies beneath the ground without <highlight>digging</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 机载技术可以让考古学家不用挖掘就能知道地底下有什么东西。

examination_example.sentence: They often include a certain amount of <highlight>digging</highlight> to test for buried materials at selected points across a landscape.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这‮勘种‬测通常包括‮某在‬一区域的选定‮点地‬进行大量挖掘来‮测检‬被埋‮质物‬。

examination_example.sentence: Some people like small talk in a meeting before <highlight>digging</highlight> into important matters, while others are more straightforward.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有些人喜欢在深入研究重要问题之前在会议上闲聊，而另一些人则更直截了当。

examination_example.sentence: Ground surveys allow archaeologists to pinpoint the places where <highlight>digs</highlight> will be successful.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 地面勘察可以让考古学家定位挖掘点。

examination_example.sentence: Oil wells weren't drilled back then; they were essentially <highlight>dug</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当时没有钻井；它们基本上是挖出来的。

examination_example.sentence: What prevented Higgins' workers from <highlight>digging</highlight> a proper hole to get the oil?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 是什么阻止了希金斯的工人挖一个合适的洞来获取石油？

examination_example.sentence: Next, Twenge's team <highlight>dug</highlight> a lite deeper into the data on screen time.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 接下来，Twenge的团队在屏幕时间上对数据进行了更深入的挖掘。

examination_example.sentence: Of the first 20,000 people who <highlight>dug</highlight> for gold, 4,000 got rich.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在前两万名挖金子的人中，有四千人发了财。

examination_example.sentence: To construct a working still, use a sharp stick or rock to <highlight>dig</highlight> a hole four feet across and three feet deep.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 要建造蒸馏器，用锋利的棍子或石块挖一个四英尺宽、三英尺深的洞。

examination_example.sentence: We were respectful of craft (技艺) and focused on <highlight>digging</highlight> into the characters we were going to play.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们尊重技艺，专注于挖掘我们要扮演的角色。
